I"<p><a href="https://simplenote.com">Simplenote</a> is a basic note-taking application developed by Automattic, the same company that created WordPress. The application is free and available on every platform, including Linux. Itâ€™s also <a href="https://simplenote.com/developers/">open source</a>. You can use Simplenote in your web browser.</p>

<p>After you download the application, youâ€™ll be prompted to create an account. That account is used to back up your notes to Automatticâ€™s servers and synchronize your notes across all of your other devices. Note that Automattic <a href="https://simplenote.com/help/#encryption">doesnâ€™t encrypt your content</a> on their servers. You canâ€™t disable the synchronizing feature.</p>

<p>Export options are limited, but the <em>Publish to Web</em> feature allows you to share your notes on the internet with a public URL.</p>

<h3 id="enabling-markdown-support">Enabling Markdown Support</h3>

<p>To enable Markdown support in Simplenote, create a note, click the Info icon, and then select <strong>Markdown Formatted</strong>.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/tools/simplenote-markdown.png" class="img-fluid" alt="Enabling Markdown support in Simplenote" style="width:30%;" /></p>

<p>The currently selected note and any new notes you create in the future will have this setting enabled automatically.</p>

